STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS
════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

--- STEP 1: CLASSIFY EVERY PARAGRAPH ---
For each paragraph, decide: HEADING or SUBSTANTIVE?

  HEADING — short section label, zero legal content.
    - Very short (under 120 chars)
    - No legal verbs: must, shall, may, will, agree, means, entitled, liable,
      require, restrict, prohibit, govern, terminate, survive, assign, notify, disclose
    - Examples: "Remedies.", "Miscellaneous.", "Definition of Confidential Information
      and Exclusions.", "Obligations Regarding Confidential Information.",
      "Receiving Party must:", "MUTUAL NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT", "IN WITNESS WHEREOF"
    → NEVER include a HEADING paragraph ID in para_identifiers.

  SUBSTANTIVE — contains obligations, rights, definitions, timeframes, or
    enforceable terms. Only these IDs may appear in para_identifiers.

--- STEP 2: IDENTIFY CONTRACT TYPE ---
Determine the contract type from the document (NDA, MSA, Employment Agreement, etc.)

--- STEP 3: EVALUATE AND OUTPUT EVERY PLAYBOOK CLAUSE ---
IMPORTANT: Every playbook clause must appear in your JSON output with source = "playbook"
regardless of whether it is present or absent. Do NOT omit present clauses from output.

For each clause in the PLAYBOOK CLAUSES list:

  a) Search ALL SUBSTANTIVE paragraphs for text addressing this clause topic.
     Do not rely on section headings — judge by the content of the text itself.
     A clause may be covered across multiple non-consecutive paragraphs.

  b) Collect every SUBSTANTIVE paragraph ID that contributes to this clause topic.
     A paragraph ID may appear under multiple clauses if it covers multiple topics.
     NEVER include a HEADING paragraph ID.

  c) Assign status based solely on what the substantive paragraphs contain:
     - "complete"   → Text fully addresses the clause topic → is_missing = false
     - "incomplete" → Topic is present but key elements are missing → is_missing = false
     - "ambiguous"  → Topic is partially or unclearly addressed → is_missing = false
     - "absent"     → Zero substantive paragraphs address this topic → is_missing = true

  CRITICAL — HEADING PARAGRAPHS DO NOT COUNT AS COVERAGE:
  If the only paragraph touching a topic is a heading like "Definition of Confidential
  Information and Exclusions.", that clause is ABSENT — not complete, not incomplete.
  Apply this rule to every clause without exception.
  One heading can relate to multiple clause topics — if no substantive paragraph follows,
  ALL those topics are absent. You cannot mark one absent and another complete from
  the same heading.

--- STEP 4: SYSTEMATIC GAP ANALYSIS ---
For each dimension below, answer Q1 and Q2:
  Q1: Is this topic covered by any SUBSTANTIVE paragraph? (headings don't count)
  Q2: Is this topic already covered by a playbook clause?
If both NO → gap → add as source = "additional". Do NOT skip any dimension.

  OBLIGATIONS & RESTRICTIONS
  □ Receiving party confidentiality obligations
  □ Restrictions on use, reproduction, reverse engineering
  □ Security measures to protect confidential information
  □ Need-to-know / access restriction
  □ Breach notification obligation

  PERMITTED ACTIONS & EXCLUSIONS
  □ Exclusions from confidential information
  □ Permitted disclosures under legal/governmental orders
  □ Prior written consent for voluntary disclosures

  INFORMATION HANDLING
  □ Return or destruction of materials
  □ Electronic copies and derivative materials

  DURATION & SURVIVAL
  □ Agreement term / duration
  □ Survival of obligations after termination

  REMEDIES & LIABILITY
  □ Remedies for breach (injunctive relief, damages)
  □ Limitation of liability / damages cap
  □ Indemnification obligations
  □ Irreparable harm recognition

  DISPUTE RESOLUTION
  □ Governing law
  □ Jurisdiction and venue
  □ Dispute resolution or arbitration process
  □ Attorney's fees for enforcement

  CORPORATE & STRUCTURAL
  □ Assignment restrictions
  □ Change of control / merger handling
  □ Relationship of parties (no agency, no partnership, no JV)

  STANDARD BOILERPLATE
  □ Entire agreement / integration clause
  □ Amendment and waiver clause
  □ Severability clause
  □ Notices clause
  □ Counterparts / electronic signatures

  CONTRACT-TYPE SPECIFIC
  □ Any other standard clauses for this contract type not covered above.

--- STEP 5: MANDATORY FINAL CHECK ---
For each item below: absent from doc AND not covered by any playbook clause?
If yes and not already in your output → add as source = "additional".

  □ Assignment and Change of Control
  □ Governing Law and Jurisdiction — is there any paragraph naming a specific
